            {
              "id": "CVE-2025-14524-libcurl4t64",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2025-14524 medium vulnerability for libcurl4t64 package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "When an OAuth2 bearer token is used for an HTTP(S) transfer, and that transfer performs a cross-protocol redirect to a second URL that uses an IMAP, LDAP, POP3 or SMTP scheme, curl might wrongly pass on the bearer token to the new target host."
